name: Hideout
description:
If you're not too fond of Patreon, I've just added a kofi link to the profile card where you can directly support us.

Your tips will go towards an Nvidia Tesla P40 (24GB) for training and fine-tuning new models.

I made some unique merges to achieve the final result and I will be including them in the additional versions because they're worth checking out.

VAE used in previews is vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors but you can use whatever one you want.

Nanachi might end up looking human if you don't use furry tags. I haven't fully used this model yet, so I don't know what exactly to expect.

This model was not designed for NSFW. Characters should be able to keep their clothes on, especially if you put NSFW in the negative prompt.

Adding links is acting strange, so I'll just name the creators for now. I'll link when linking is fixed

credits:

Pastel-Mix - andite

Realistic vision v2.0 - SG_161222

MIA704 - Goldkoron

Rev Animated - s6yx

There could be more, but I don't remember the entire process. If I think of anymore, I'll add them here.

This is from the creators of the MIA model:

I recommend using the following always at beginning of your positive prompt: masterpiece, best quality;

I recommend using the following always as negative prompt: lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, text, error, missing fingers, extra digit, fewer digits, cropped, worst quality, low quality, normal quality, jpeg artifacts, signature, watermark, username, blurry

(These are NovelAI's prompt template settings)

PROMPT FORMAT: Character, tag1, tag2, etc; Character2, tag 1, tag2, etc; Location (this is the format the model is trained with, it's not necessary but recommended for best results)

explanation for this prompt format: Commas separate subtags for a major concept or character while semicolons act as major concept separators for generating multiple characters or marking the location at end of prompt.

EXAMPLES:

masterpiece, best quality; Riko, shift dress, red whistle; orphanage

masterpiece, best quality; Riko, delver outfit, red whistle; Reg, aubade helmet, aubade cape, backpack; upper second layer

masterpiece, best quality; Riko, delver outfit, red whistle; Reg, aubade helmet, aubade cape, arm extended; lower second layer, seeker camp

masterpiece, best quality; Habo, black whistle; Reg, aubade cape; the first layer, eternal fortunes

If struggling to generate a character solo, try adding tags like "masterpiece, best quality, solo; Riko, shift dress, red whistle; orphanage"

CHARACTERS AND UNIQUE SUBTAGS:

Riko

shift dress (dress she wears in Orth)

cold outfit (she wears this in the fifth layer in the movie)

arm extended

Shiggy (Shiggy had issues when captioning "red whistle" so I had to caption all of his images without it otherwise he would never get his red eye color. Generating him as a result will always try to generate something in place of his red whistle unless you add the red whistle tag for it to understand)
